summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 3455, entitled "An Ordinance regulating the business of conveying persons, from place to place for hire by the use of vehicles drawn by animals in the City of Seattle, and providing penalties for the violation of the provisions thereof, and repealing Ordinance No. 3274, entitled "An Ordinance to license and regulate the business of conveying persons, goods and things from place to place for hire by the use of vehicles drawn by animals within the City of Seattle", approved March 15, 1894," approved July 16, 1894.
